# shadcn/ui and Tailwind CSS

## Class Name Utilities
- Always use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` (tailwind-merge + clsx)
- Never use inline styles or `!important`
- Prefer Tailwind utility classes over custom CSS

## Component Usage
- Prefer shadcn components over raw HTML
- Use shadcn components from `@/components/ui/`
- Extend shadcn components when needed, don't modify source

## Styling Patterns
```typescript
// Good: Use cn() for conditional classes
<Button className={cn("base-classes", isActive && "active-classes")} />

// Bad: Inline styles or !important
<Button style={{ color: 'red' }} />
<Button className="!text-red" />
```

## Dark Mode
- Use Tailwind dark mode classes: `dark:bg-background`
- Test both light and dark themes
- Use CSS variables from shadcn theme

## Responsive Design
- Use Tailwind breakpoints: `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:`
- Mobile-first approach
- Test on multiple screen sizes

## Component Composition
- Compose shadcn components to build complex UIs
- Don't duplicate shadcn component code
- Create wrapper components in modules when needed
